    "verifyText": {
      "id": "lf-help-tooltip-text",
      "value": "A regular IRA is also called a traditional IRA. It is a tax-deferred retirement account. For 2025, you are allowed to make a tax-deferred contribution of $7,000 to a regular IRA. This account grows tax-deferred until you begin to take distributions, which you may do without penalty after you turn age 59-1/2. For persons who are age 50 or older, a special catch-up provision of the 2001 tax law allows you to contribute an additional $1,000, or a total of $8,000."
